config.AddedNPCsAffectPerfection.name: Added NPCs Affect Perfection
config.AddedNPCsAffectPerfection.descrip: Whether you need to reach maximum heart with NPCs added by this mod to reach 100% perfection in-game. This won't have any effect if player already reach 100% perfection.
ItsBenterKarl.Name: Karl
ItsBenterKarl.Gifts_Loved: You've got a keen eye for what I like. Much thanks @.
ItsBenterKarl.Gifts_Liked: Thank you, @. You've made my day brighter.
ItsBenterKarl.Gifts_Neutral: Oh, you got me a little something
ItsBenterKarl.Gifts_Disliked: Well, this is, um, quite unexpected. Thanks, @.
ItsBenterKarl.Gifts_Hated: Well, I never expected to get something like this.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.00H-1: Office life can be a grind, but it pays the bills.#$e#That's one reason I'm here. $1
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.00H-2: Fishing, a total fine way to take a break from the work.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.00H-3: I've heard this town has some great fishing spots, so I thought I'd try my luck.#$e#So far, I'm totally not disappointed. $1
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.00H-Winter-1: Ah, @, it's one good winter's day today, and I can't help but admire the beauty of this season.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.02H-1: These parts are real peaceful. A nice break from the city's chaos.#$e#Anyway, nice talking to you. Maybe we'll bump into each other while I'm out fishing.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.02H-2: Hey there, @. Have you checked out the fishing spots around Pelican Town yet? Some real gems here.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.02H-3: Let's keep these conversations going. It's nice to have a friendly face to talk to in this new place.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.02H-4: Been trying out all different fishing techniques lately, figuring what works best in these waters.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.02H-5: Hmmm... Ice cream after dinner would be very nice. %revealtaste:ItsBenterKarl:(O)233 #$e#Oh, I'm just planning for a good time. $1
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.02H-6: I've heard the riverbank is a good place to fish. Have you had any luck there?
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.02H-Winter-1: Have you had the chance to explore the valley in winter? The snowy woods and those frosty mountains, they're sights to behold, I tell you.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.02H-Summer-1: Hey, @, what a perfect summer day! It's the ideal time to be outdoors and, of course, to fish. $1
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.04H-1: Back in the city, it's all concrete and hustle. Could sure use a break from that.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.04H-2: So, @, how's your journey in Pelican Town been so far? Finding your place in this community?
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.04H-3: If you ever need some fishing tips, just give me the word. I've picked up a trick or two over the years.#$e#Speaking of the weather, just make sure you check how it will go weather before you head out fishing. Rainy days can be real good for certain catches.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.04H-4: What's your favorite spot to fish around here? I'd love some recommendations.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.04H-Summer-1: Fishing in the summer has its own unique charm. The warmth of the sun, the gentle breeze, it all adds to the experience.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.06H-1: Hello there, @. It's nice seeing you again.#$b#You know, I'm starting to feel like we're becoming friends. $1
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.06H-2: Have you had any memorable fishing tales in the valley? I'd sure love to hear about them.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.06H-3: It's important to put in an honest day's work.#$b#That just how I was raised.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.06H-4: My wife, might not understand me and fishing, but she respects how it brings me joy.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.06H-5: Work is work, there's the ups and the downs.#$b#I'm mighty thankful for the time I have in the valley.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.06H-6: Fishing is a bit like life, you know? Sometimes you get a big catch, and other times, you have to be patient and enjoy the moment.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.06H-7: You know, I once shaved off my mustache as a dare at work. Regretted it instantly, but it made for a good laugh. $1
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.08H-1: Sometimes, when fishing, everything just drifts away.#$b#It's like a meditation, but slightly more productive.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.08H-2: Growing up in a village was something special. Life was simpler back then. $2
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.08H-3: For what it's worth, my job has provided a sense of stability, which has allowed me rediscover my love for fishing.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.08H-4: *yawn* I got caught late at work last night. #$e#Not the best, but there's not much use in complaining here.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.08H-5: Them peeps at the office, they're like family. Make workdays much more enjoyable.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.08H-6: Work, even in the bustling city, has its own kind of beauty. It's where I've honed my craft and found my place.#$e#There's a certain satisfaction in giving your all to a task and seeing it through to the end.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.08H-7: While I'm deeply grateful my moments of escape here in Pelican Town, my work in the city has its own set of rewards.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.08H-Winter-1: You know, it's kinda funny how the seasons stir up such strong feelings and memories, @. #$b#There's something truly special about sitting by the fireplace on a chilly day, ain't there?
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.08H-Fall-1: My wife likes fall so much. She's so pleased seeing leaves start turning to those vibrant shades of red and gold.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.10H-1: My parents were hardworking folks, I sure hope I make them proud.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.10H-2: Pelican Town offers some of the best fishing spots I've ever encountered.#$b#This place is a total paradise for anglers.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.10H-3: Hey, @, good to see you again. We've become real good friends, haven't we? $1
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.10H-4: You know, talking to you can be like a breath of fresh air.#$e#Oh, my work peeps are more than fine, I guess it's the different place and time. $1
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.10H-5: All in all, it's about finding a balance between dedication to your career and the simple joys of life.#$e#This is like fishing here in Pelican Town.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.10H-6: Emma and I have talked a lot about the importance of finding balance in our lives. She understands that Pelican Town is my escape.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.10H-7: My career is progressing well. It provides financial stability and a future for Emma and I.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.10H-8: My job in the city may have its challenges, but it's also where I've found some good friends.#$b#We often share stories and experiences, and they've been a great source of encouragement#$e#I'm grateful for all the good I have. $1
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.spring_5: Hey @, hope everything on %farm farm is going well and ready for the year ahead.
ItsBenterKarl.Dialogue.spring_13: I was chatting with Lewis. The mayor got quite a story about egg festival he attended in his younger days.
ItsBenterDiane.Name: Diane
ItsBenterDiane.Gifts_Loved: Oh, @, you truly have a discerning taste! This is absolutely splendid.
ItsBenterDiane.Gifts_Liked: This is a lovely gesture. You have a good eye @.
ItsBenterDiane.Gifts_Neutral: A gift? Well, tt's always interesting to see what people choose.
ItsBenterDiane.Gifts_Disliked: This isn't quite to my taste. But thank you for thinking of me.
ItsBenterDiane.Gifts_Hated: I must be honest, @, this gift of yours leaves me a bit baffled.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.00H-1: Greetings, dear. I trust you're well today?
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.00H-2: I find the architecture in this town rather quaint. Charming on its way.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.00H-3: Ah, the seasons in this region are so much more... pronounced than what I'm used to.#$e#Can't really help it when nature isn't given the space in the city.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.00H-4: I've always found the charm of small towns like this rather curious.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.00H-5: The town's museum has been getting quite a bit of attention, I hear.#$e#Quite unexpected, most would think the town would prioritize resources on other areas.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.00H-6: I've heard some talk about the local farming community. How fascinating.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.00H-7: The simplicity of life here is a stark contrast to how it usually is for me.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.02H-1: You know, I've always had a soft spot for old books. Suppose the town library must hold a number of them.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.02H-2: The townspeople seem to enjoy your company. I suppose that's something.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.02H-3: I've been looking into studies on Dwarves's fabric of society lately. It's truly captivating.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.02H-4: I've developed a fondness for the local museum. Any favorite collection?
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.02H-5: Do you find the simplicity of life here comforting, or is it something you've had to adjust to?
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.02H-6: Greetings, dear. I'm sorry if I seem a bit under the weather. $2#$b#Life has a way of wearing me down, I'm afraid.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.02H-7: What do you suppose keeps people tied to this place, generation after generation?
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.02H-8: Mayor Lewis has been at the helm of Pelican Town for quite some time, hasn't he? His dedication must amount to something.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.02H-9: I'm not feeling my usual self today. A touch of fatigue, perhaps. $2
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.02H-Fall-1: Fall is the perfect time for leisurely walks, wrapped in cozy scarves, and taking in the beauty of the changing landscape.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.02H-Fall-2: I find that the fall season awakens a sense of nostalgia, reminding us of the passage of time and the beauty in change.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.02H-Summer-1: Ah, the changing seasons in Stardew Valley. While each has its own charm, I must admit a fondness for the milder ones.#$e#Summer can be a bit too scorching for my taste.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.02H-Winter-1: Winter's biting cold can be invigorating, but it also calls for layers of heavy clothing, which I find rather cumbersome.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.04H-1: I must say, your presence has added a touch of warmth to this quaint little town.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.04H-2: You know, my interest in archaeology has already been there since my childhood. I used to spend hours reading about ancient civilizations and imagining myself on grand adventures.#$b#Too bad we can't always have what we dream of.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.04H-3: The rhythms of Pelican Town have become a part of my life, unexpected but inevitable I'd say.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.04H-4: The close-knit nature of this community is evident in the way they come together to celebrate festivals and special occasions.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.04H-5: I apologize if I appear distant. My energy levels are quite low. $2
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.04H-6: Sometimes, I feel like a bit of an outsider. It's refreshing to have someone like you to talk to.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.04H-7: The residents of Pelican Town have a remarkable sense of community. It's something to be admired.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.04H-8: I find that I appreciate the simpler gatherings in Pelican Town more than the grand affairs in the city. It's much more refreshing here.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.04H-9: I've noticed that Gunther dedicates nearly all his time to the museum. I worry he's missing out on other enriching experiences. $2
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.04H-Spring-1: I find Spring's delicate blooms and the chirping of birds to be a soothing backdrop for mind to wander freely.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.04H-Spring-2: Spring's signifies a fresh start and renewed hope, which I find both comforting and inspiring.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.04H-Spring-3: While I may not be the most outdoorsy person, I do cherish the opportunities Spring weather provides for peaceful reflection.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.06H-1: Sometimes, I get lost in the archives, poring over old records and documents. It's like piecing together a puzzle of the past.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.06H-2: I've come to admire farmers and their unwavering dedication to the land. Their hard work shapes the very essence of this valley.#$b#And yes, that includes you @.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.06H-3: I've come to appreciate the clean, crisp air here. It does wonders for one's well-being.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.06H-4: Isn't the air in Stardew Valley simply invigorating? It's a welcome change from the city's pollution.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.06H-5: Paintings can evoke such profound emotions. I often find myself lost in the stories they tell.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.06H-6: The children here are so full of curiosity and potential. I often wonder what the future holds for them.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.06H-7: One of my cherished book discoveries is 'Chatters of the Past'#$b#It's a historical novel that offers a glimpse into the life of ordinaries on the decades past.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.06H-8: The changing seasons here are so beautifully reflected in the landscape.#$e#It's tragic, yet comforting that the beauty is fleeting.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.06H-9: My body is telling me to take it easy today. Perhaps a gentle stroll in the fresh air will help.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.06H-10: Greetings, my dear @. I hope the day finds you in good spirits.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.08H-1: There's a certain charm to the imperfections of this town that I've grown quite fond of. It's a reminder that beauty can be found in the most unexpected places.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.08H-2: You know, I've always found solace in the company of old books. The smell of aged pages, the knowledge preserved through the ages... it's like stepping into a different world.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.08H-3: The art of storytelling has always fascinated me. I've been reading up on the local legends and folklore lately.#$e#We'd never know if there's fragments of truth in the words of the alleged fictions.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.08H-4: Pelican Town has a unique charm, shaped by the incredible individuals who call it home. I'm honored to be a part of their world.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.08H-5: I've always been intrigued by the stories behind the artifacts I collect. Each piece has a history, a narrative waiting to be uncovered.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.08H-6: Pelican Town's museum has become an integral part of the community.#$b#I take great pride in being a witness of that legacy being built.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.08H-7: I've been invited to a charity fundraiser next week. While the cause is noble, I often find such gatherings a bit... disingenuous.#$b#Not that I can help myself being upright on such occasion. $1
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.08H-8: Sometimes I have to make appearance at a business gathering. Networking is an essential part of the family's world, you see.#$e#There's a certain elegance to social events, but they're far from a genuine connection. It just the way it's meant to be.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.08H-9: You know, Gunther and I have developed a routine when it comes to cataloging new collection pieces. It's a meticulous process, but oh, so rewarding. $1
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.10H-1: You're more than just a friend; you're a kindred spirit. I value our friendship immensely.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.10H-2: I've always been drawn to the idea of leaving a legacy, something more profound than just wealth. Perhaps that's why I admire peering into the past.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.10H-3: My schedule can be quite packed, between sorting pieces in the city, hubbub of the events, and the rhytm in valley. That said, I wouldn't have it any other way. $1
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.10H-4: My husband's business keeps him away for long stretches, which can be lonely at times. But the love remains unwavering.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.10H-5: Museum stands as a symbol of the commitment to preserving legacy and embracing a brighter future. A true gem of a community.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.10H-6: I often tell my husband that the valley's air has done wonders for my overall well-being. It's truly a blessing to be here.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.10H-7: The war with the Gotoro Empire has left a lasting impact on so many lives. It weighs heavily on my heart. $2#$e#This would be a part history that left you with lasting bitterness when studied. $2
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.10H-8: In my recent reading of 'Purple Beret', it has stirred profound reflections within me, most notably on the plight of the children affected by the ravages of war.#$e#The toll of war extends far beyond the battlefield. It reaches into the hearts of families and communities.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.10H-9: To love and to be loved is to embrace the ebb and flow of life, knowing that together, you'll navigate the currents with grace.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.10H-10: Ah, @, what a delight to cross paths with you.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.10H-Curator-1: The moments when visitors are genuinely captivated by the exhibits are the most rewarding. It's a reminder of why I do what I do.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.10H-Curator-2: I often collaborate with fellow historians and archaeologists, exchanging knowledge and artifacts to enrich our understanding.#$e#We all stand on the shoulders of giants.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.10H-Curator-3: Managing all sort of these new affairs can be demanding, but I thrive on the sense of purpose it brings to my life.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.10H-Curator-4: One of the challenges of curating a museum is maintaining the delicate balance between preservation and accessibility.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.10H-Curator-5: The museum's exhibits may seem static, but they constantly evolve as new discoveries are made. It's a thrilling process.
ItsBenterDiane.Dialogue.10H-Curator-6: I've been fortunate to witness the impact of the museum on the lives of its visitors, sparking their curiosity and igniting a love for history and knowledge.
ItsBenterPaolo.Name: Paolo
